How to install in WIN32 environment.

You need Borland C++ compiler 5.0 in C:\bc5.

C:\global>win32\makeall[RET]
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
C:\global>win32\install[RET]
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
C:\global>mkdir \tmp[RET]
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
C:\global>win32\clean[RET]
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
You need perl command when using htags.pl.
You can get win32-perl at Active STATE. See 'http://www.activestate.com/'.

Also, you need UNIX compatible sed and sort.
Please read win32.txt by Dan Fandrich for more information.

Global 3.5 has been tested under Windows NT 4.0 with Borland C++ 5.02.
